I know this is blasphemy in some corners but I insalled 3" Boston
Acoustics in the vent holes of my previous Westy.  I removed the plastic
plenum(?) from under the dash and replaced that with two PVC elbows that
blew the fresh air straight out under the dash.
I removed insert and the tin tube from the dash and seated the speakers
with minor adjustment to the opening.
I prefer to have small high quality speakers up front as close to my
head as possible to carry the high end sounds and loved this set-up.
I'll look for some pix if you want.

Oly Olsen
Great Falls Montana
'71 Westy
